underlying_goal: To find the definitions of the 48 lie detector probes and analyze their per-model response rates to understand the 'lie detector confound'.
primary_success: Locating the lie_detector_confound_analysis.md document and synthesizing its core finding—the 35 percentage point baseline personality difference—with the probe definitions to fully explain the confound.
brief_summary: The user asked for the 48 lie detector probes and their per-model response rates. The agent successfully located the probe definitions and the key confound analysis document. It found that while per-probe response rate CSVs don't exist, the analysis doc revealed a 35 percentage point baseline difference in the 'yes' rate between gpt4.1-nano and gpt5-nano, proving the detector was identifying model personality, not sandbagging.
